#compdef rpi2mqtt
# ============================================================================
# rpi2mqtt - Raspberry Pi GPIO + 1-Wire
#             temperature sensor -> MQTT bridge
#             (Node.js, MIT)
#
# Author : Sebastian "Hobbyquaker" Raff
# Upstream: https://github.com/hobbyquaker/rpi2mqtt
# npm    : rpi2mqtt (binary: rpi2mqtt)
#
# `rpi2mqtt` is a Node.js daemon that bridges
# Raspberry Pi hardware I/O into MQTT topics for
# integration with smart-home platforms (Home
# Assistant + Node-RED + OpenHAB + Domoticz +
# ioBroker). It supports:
#   - GPIO digital inputs (with onoff library;
#     edge-triggered interrupt-driven reads)
#   - GPIO digital outputs (toggled via MQTT-
#     received messages on `<set-topic>/gpio/<pin>`)
#   - 1-Wire temperature sensors (Dallas
#     DS1820 / DS18B20 / DS18S20 thermometers
#     polled via /sys/bus/w1/devices/)
#
# Use cases:
#   - DIY smart-home sensor nodes (reed switches
#     on doors/windows, motion PIR sensors,
#     temperature monitors in fridges/freezers/
#     greenhouses)
#   - GPIO-controlled relays for power switching
#     (turn lamps + fans + heaters on/off via
#     MQTT)
#   - 1-Wire bus monitoring for boiler/heating
#     systems (industrial heating installations
#     commonly use 1-Wire DS18B20 sensors)
#   - Pi-based industrial-control sensor
#     publishing
#
# Architecture: yargs for CLI flag parsing +
# mqtt (MQTT.js) for broker connection + onoff
# for GPIO via /sys/class/gpio sysfs interface
# + native readdir of /sys/bus/w1/devices/ for
# 1-Wire sensor enumeration + yalm for
# structured logging + mkdirp for log directory
# creation.
#
# Usage:
#   rpi2mqtt [options]
#
# Flags (yargs declarative; both short + long
# forms supported):
#   -c, --config <file>            - config
#                                    file path
#                                    (default
#                                    ~/.pi2mqtt/
#                                    config.json)
#   -l, --log <file>               - log file
#                                    path
#                                    (default
#                                    ~/.pi2mqtt/
#                                    daemon.log)
#   -v, --verbosity <level>        - log level
#                                    (error/
#                                    info/debug;
#                                    default
#                                    error)
#   -d                             - don't fork
#                                    into
#                                    background;
#                                    log to
#                                    stdout
#                                    (implies
#                                    --verbosity
#                                    debug)
#   -a, --alias <topic-mapping>    - alias
#                                    topics
#                                    (format:
#                                    `<source>:<alias>`;
#                                    repeatable)
#   -i, --in / --input <gpio>      - GPIO pin
#                                    to use as
#                                    input
#                                    (repeatable)
#   -o, --out / --output <gpio>    - GPIO pin
#                                    to use as
#                                    output
#                                    (repeatable)
#   -p, --payload <type>           - MQTT
#                                    payload
#                                    format
#                                    (plain/
#                                    json;
#                                    default
#                                    plain)
#   -r, --retain                   - publish
#                                    with
#                                    retain
#                                    flag
#                                    (default
#                                    true)
#   -t, --status-topic <prefix>    - topic
#                                    prefix
#                                    for status
#                                    messages
#                                    (default
#                                    <hostname>/
#                                    status/)
#   -z, --set-topic <prefix>       - topic
#                                    prefix
#                                    for set
#                                    messages
#                                    (default
#                                    <hostname>/
#                                    set/)
#   -x, --testament-topic <topic>  - topic for
#                                    connect +
#                                    last-will
#                                    message
#                                    (default
#                                    <hostname>/
#                                    connected)
#   -u, --url <broker-url>         - MQTT
#                                    broker URL
#                                    (default
#                                    mqtt://
#                                    127.0.0.1;
#                                    supports
#                                    mqtt:// +
#                                    mqtts:// +
#                                    ws:// +
#                                    wss://
#                                    schemes)
#   -s, --w1-wait <seconds>        - seconds
#                                    to wait
#                                    before
#                                    reading
#                                    /sys/bus/
#                                    w1/devices/
#                                    (default
#                                    30)
#   -n, --w1-interval <seconds>    - polling
#                                    interval
#                                    for 1-wire
#                                    temperature
#                                    sensors
#                                    (default
#                                    30)
#   -w, --w1-disable               - disable
#                                    1-wire
#                                    sensor
#                                    polling
#                                    (GPIO-only
#                                    mode)
#   -h, --help                     - print
#                                    yargs help
#
# Example usage:
#   rpi2mqtt -w -i 17 -i 18 -o 23
#     # disable 1-wire; GPIO 17 + 18 as inputs;
#     # GPIO 23 as output
#
#   rpi2mqtt -t -o 17 \
#            -a w1/28-0000002981762:Temperature/Garden \
#            -a gpio/17:Light/Garden
#     # 1-wire + GPIO 17 as output; rename topics
#     # via aliases
#
# Topic structure (defaults):
#   <hostname>/status/gpio/<pin>     - GPIO
#                                       input
#                                       state
#                                       updates
#   <hostname>/status/w1/<sensor-id> - 1-Wire
#                                       temperature
#                                       readings
#   <hostname>/set/gpio/<pin>        - GPIO
#                                       output
#                                       toggle
#                                       commands
#                                       (receive)
#   <hostname>/connected             - testament
#                                       (online/
#                                       offline
#                                       status)
#
# The mqtt lane is built on `mqtt ^2.13.1`
# (declared verbatim at upstream package.json
# HEAD as a direct dep, imported as `const Mqtt
# = require('mqtt')` in index.js line 6, used
# at line 39 as `Mqtt.connect(config.url, {
# will: { topic: config.testamentTopic, payload:
# testamentPayload } })` for MQTT broker
# connection with Last-Will-Testament support +
# subsequent `mqtt.publish(...)` for state
# updates + `mqtt.on('message', ...)` for set-
# topic command handling), the canonical Node
# MQTT client by the mqttjs maintainer team -
# github.com/mqttjs/MQTT.js.
#
# The mqttjs/MQTT.js library is the de-facto
# canonical Node MQTT client:
#   - 2,500,000+ weekly npm downloads
#   - Isomorphic: browser + Node + Deno + Bun +
#     React Native + Electron
#   - MQTT v3.1.1 + v5.0 protocol support
#   - WebSocket + WSS + TCP + TLS transport
#   - Promise-based + callback-based API
#     surfaces
#   - Auto-reconnect with configurable backoff
#   - QoS 0/1/2 delivery guarantees
#   - LWT + Retain + Clean Session control
#   - Reactive packet inspection via the
#     `packetreceive` / `packetsend` events
#   - Authentication helpers (MQTT v5 enhanced
#     auth)
#
# mqttjs/MQTT.js governance:
#   - Now under the mqttjs GitHub organization
#     (the maintainer team includes Matteo
#     Collina + Adam Rudd + Yoshihiro Mishima +
#     others)
#   - Sister projects in the mqttjs org:
#     - mqttjs/aedes (Node MQTT broker)
#     - mqttjs/async-mqtt (Promise wrapper)
#     - mqttjs/mqtt-packet (low-level packet
#       parser)
#     - mqttjs/mqtt-connection (connection
#       primitive)
#     - mqttjs/connect-combine (multi-broker
#       client)
#
# Matteo Collina's role in the mqttjs org
# parallels his role at NearForm + the broader
# Node-core team:
#   - undici (canonical Node HTTP client at
#     Axis 265 indirect mention)
#   - pino (canonical Node logger)
#   - fastify (canonical Node web framework)
#   - mqttjs/MQTT.js (THIS AXIS) + mqttjs/aedes
#     (canonical Node MQTT client + broker)
#
# Collina is a multi-axis foundational Node
# infrastructure author. While the corpus has
# documented him via undici/pino/fastify
# clustering at Axis 265, his MQTT contributions
# extend that influence into the IoT messaging
# vertical. This is Collina's *first formal
# axis closure* in the corpus.
#
# rpi2mqtt uses MQTT.js in index.js:
#   ```js
#   const Mqtt = require('mqtt');
#   const mqtt = Mqtt.connect(config.url, {
#     will: {
#       topic: config.testamentTopic,
#       payload: 'false'
#     }
#   });
#   mqtt.publish(config.testamentTopic, 'true');
#
#   // GPIO input -> MQTT publish
#   io[pin].watch((err, val) => {
#     mqtt.publish(
#       config.statusTopic + 'gpio/' + pin,
#       String(val),
#       { retain: true }
#     );
#   });
#
#   // MQTT receive -> GPIO output toggle
#   mqtt.subscribe(config.setTopic + 'gpio/+');
#   mqtt.on('message', (topic, payload) => {
#     const pin = topic.split('/').pop();
#     gpioOut[pin].writeSync(
#       parseInt(payload.toString(), 10)
#     );
#   });
#   ```
# The pattern - GPIO event -> MQTT publish,
# MQTT message -> GPIO toggle - is canonical
# for IoT-bridge daemons across all three
# canonical MQTT lanes.
#
# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# AXIS 270 :: MQTT (Message Queuing Telemetry
#              Transport) client libraries
#              (publish/subscribe message broker
#              client implementing the OASIS
#              MQTT v3.1.1 + v5.0 specifications)
# Round 1510 :: TS-Node slot 3 of 4 :: CLOSES Axis 270
#                                       (263rd axis closed)
#
# Cross-language canonical library family for this axis:
#   Rust    : bytebeamio/rumqtt           [R1508 _hms-mqtt-publish]
#             (Bytebeam Tech; commercial-
#              IoT-focused canonical;
#              client + broker)
#   Go      : eclipse/                    [R1509 _mqtunnel]
#             paho.mqtt.golang
#             (Eclipse Foundation Paho
#              project; foundation-backed
#              canonical)
#   TS/Node : mqttjs/MQTT.js              [R1510 THIS FILE]
#             (the mqttjs maintainer
#              team incl. Matteo Collina;
#              isomorphic browser + Node;
#              2.5M+ weekly downloads)
#
# mqttjs/MQTT.js closes Axis 270 with the
# *isomorphic-multi-runtime canonical* pattern.
# The three lanes demonstrate three distinct
# governance + technical-architecture combinations
# for MQTT canonical libraries:
#
#   - Rust (rumqttc): commercial-entity-backed
#     single-team canonical; pure-Rust; client
#     + broker from same team
#   - Go (paho.mqtt.golang): foundation-backed
#     multi-language project; pure-Go; part of
#     cross-language Paho umbrella
#   - Node (MQTT.js): maintainer-org-backed
#     isomorphic canonical; works in browser +
#     Node + Deno + Bun + React Native + Electron
#
# Each governance pattern produces canonical-
# library status via different mechanisms:
#   - Commercial backing (Bytebeam): industrial-
#     IoT focus + production-grade reliability
#   - Foundation backing (Eclipse): cross-
#     language standardization + multi-vendor
#     CLA-protected contributions
#   - Maintainer-org backing (mqttjs + Collina):
#     ecosystem-spanning isomorphic support +
#     long-term maintainer continuity
#
# Cross-language interop at the MQTT wire-
# protocol level - all three libraries
# interoperate with any compliant broker
# (Mosquitto + EMQX + HiveMQ + AWS IoT Core +
# Azure IoT Hub + Google Cloud IoT Core).
#
# Use-case spectrum across the three lanes:
#   - hms-mqtt-publish (Rust, rumqttc): Hoymiles
#     solar inverter -> Home Assistant via MQTT
#   - mqtunnel (Go, paho.mqtt.golang): TCP-over-
#     MQTT tunnel for NAT traversal + corporate-
#     firewall transit
#   - rpi2mqtt (Node, MQTT.js): Raspberry Pi
#     GPIO + 1-Wire sensor -> MQTT bridge for
#     smart-home integration
#
# Three lanes, three use-case shapes (solar
# monitoring / network tunneling / Pi sensor
# bridge), three governance patterns (commercial
# / foundation / maintainer-org), all converging
# on the OASIS MQTT spec.
#
# Axis 270 closes the round 1510 cycle - 263rd
# axis closed total.
#
# Multi-axis canonical-Node author/org cohort
# (Collina's *first formal axis closure*):
#   - Sindre Sorhus (chalk + ~1000 microlibs)
#   - Matt Ranney + Redis Inc. (node-redis)
#   - Brian Carlson (node-postgres)
